column2: Rainy summer so far.  Smell of decaying algae on shore.
Algae bloom experienced in June.  Usually occurs in august so we were alarmed.  Holding very clear now.
Overcast- misting- following a busy traffic sat. and a big rainstorm during the night.
Rain and rising water- we have issued a plan to restrict boating!
Considering stronger action to restrict boating
Shore damage considerable- trying to restrict boat activity.  Lake level: very high
Shore damage considerable.  Lake level: very high
Algae bloom- persistent since mid July.

Small clumps of algae like plant material floating about.
Cloudy- .75" of rain in 2 days ago.
Windy- 15-20 mph southwest- wave height 10-15 cm.
Calm water.  Little if any wind.
No observations on lake condition. weather clear- wind calm- 40 degrees air temp.
Sunny- warm at 70 degrees- and light breeze.
Clear and calm.  60 degrees air temp.

overcast - cool spring - lake level up
sunny- calm - lake level continues to rise

sunny and calm - loon still here

perfect conditions- slight breeze- sunny- in a canoe for close surface contact.
